# precis-mcp ‚Äî Devin project brief (port of CLAUDE.md, no worktrees)

> **Two surfaces ‚Äî don't confuse them.** This repo IS the precis MCP server.
> The `precis` MCP tools/skills in your session are the PRODUCT's runtime
> surface ‚Äî not dev aids. To develop the repo, read: `docs/codebase.md`
> (orientation) ‚Üí `docs/architecture/state-map.md` (subsystem status) ‚Üí
> `docs/architecture/glossary.md` ‚Üí `docs/decisions/` (ADRs). Conventions,
> workflow, definition-of-done: `AGENTS.md`. No CHANGELOG ‚Äî history is
> `git log`. Backlog: `OPEN-ITEMS.md` (open work only; delete an entry in
> the same commit that completes it).

## Session workflow (feature branch ‚Üí ship)

1. Work on a **feature branch** (never directly on `main` ‚Äî see guards).
2. Implement, test, iterate (`scripts/test`).
3. Ship: `scripts/ship "msg"` ‚Äî commit WIP ‚Üí sync onto origin/main ‚Üí
   container gate (ruff/format/mypy/pytest) ‚Üí squash-merge to main.
   Idempotent; fix and re-run on a red gate. Deploy: `scripts/deploy`.
   Workflows: /land (ship), /go (ship+deploy), /whatneedsdoing.

## Token discipline (Claude Code had hooks; here it's manual)

- **`rtk` compresses noisy command output** (token-killer proxy;
  `brew install rtk`). There is NO auto-rewrite hook in Devin sessions ‚Äî
  **prefix manually**: `rtk git status`, `rtk psql -- ‚Ä¶`, `rtk grep/rg/find`,
  `rtk err -- <cmd>` (errors only, propagates exit code), `rtk summary --
  <cmd>` (heuristic digest, always exits 0 ‚Äî don't gate on it). Output is a
  DIGEST, not raw: if a detail is missing, re-run raw or read the teed log.
  Don't wrap `scripts/test` (already terse) or interactive commands.
  Project filters: `.rtk/filters.toml` (committed). Full guidance: the
  `quiet-output` skill (served from `.claude/skills/`, picked up here too).
- **`scripts/coderef callers|deps <file.py::Sym>`** for exact who-calls /
  what-depends-on before grep ‚Äî no same-named false positives (also
  `imports|importers`; `-h` for verbs). Grep stays right for text,
  non-Python, or a symbol you can't name yet.
- Cite code by durable anchor in docs/memory: `path/file.py::Qual.name`,
  not `file.py:LINE` (rots). `scripts/coderef anchor|resolve|check`.

## Guards (enforced by hooks in Claude Code; hard rules here)

- **Never `git commit` on `main`.** Work on a feature branch; `scripts/ship`
  is the only path to main.
- **Never edit a sealed migration** (`src/precis/migrations/*.sql` already on
  origin/main) or `migrations/baseline/*` ‚Äî forward-only (ADR 0005); ship a
  NEW migration. Baseline regenerates via `scripts/bump`, never by hand.
- **Prod SQL is read-only by default.** `scripts/prod-psql "SELECT ‚Ä¶"` for
  peeking at precis_prod; it connects as write-capable `agent_rw`, so any
  INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE/DDL needs the user's explicit go-ahead.
- **The session `precis` MCP writes PROD ‚Äî dogfood READ-ONLY.** DB-backed
  kinds (todo/gripe/memory/paper/‚Ä¶) target precis_prod; use read verbs only
  (`search`/`get`/`more`). File-kinds (markdown/plaintext/tex) are sandboxed
  and fine. Write-path testing: dev-DB precis via `scripts/dev`, never the
  session MCP.
- **No bare `git stash` / `stash pop`** (stack is shared with other
  checkouts). Prefer a WIP commit; else `git stash push -u -m "<tag>"` +
  `git stash apply <sha>`.

## Conventions that bite

- **Tests via `scripts/test`** (pytest in the dev container, test DB wired,
  terse output). Don't hand-roll `uv run pytest`: the torch-free host throws
  spurious ModuleNotFoundError for `marker`, `sentence_transformers`, ‚Ä¶.
  `scripts/test tests/test_x.py -k ‚Ä¶` for subsets; `scripts/test --impacted`
  (testmon) is the tightest loop. Lint/types on host: `uv run ruff check .`,
  `uv run ruff format --check .`, `uv run mypy src tests`.
- **`uv` for everything** ‚Äî never bare pip/pytest/mypy. Ruff replaces
  black/isort/flake8. All tool config in pyproject.toml.
- **Container-first ops.** `scripts/dev` ‚Üí dev shell; `scripts/db` ‚Üí local
  psql (dev pgvector at 127.0.0.1:5432, user postgres); never reaches prod.
- **Don't mutate body chunks** (`ord >= 0` rows are append-only): to
  "update", DELETE + INSERT so the embedding/summary cascade re-runs.
- **Embeddings fill via the worker, not ingest** (ADR 0007).
- **Outbound HTTP through `safe_fetch`** (`src/precis/utils/safe_fetch.py`)
  ‚Äî raw `httpx‚Ä¶get(url, follow_redirects=True)` is an SSRF.
- **Skills are runtime docs**: `src/precis/data/skills/` is the agent-facing
  channel served via `get(kind='skill')`.
- Keep docs true: a subsystem change updates `state-map.md` (and
  `docs/codebase.md` if the shape changed) in the same commit.
- Always use ssh to git pull/push. Never commit secrets. GitHub Actions
  pinned by commit SHA.
